    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">792.94/14</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Siamese Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prince Damras</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-21">May 21,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of
                    your confidential letter of May 18, 1935, to Mr. Hornbeck, in which reference is
                    made to certain recent press despatches in regard to the foreign relations of
                    Siam, and in which assurance is conveyed that it is the policy of His Majesty’s
                    Government to strengthen the bonds of friendship with all the treaty Powers
                    alike, and not with any single one in particular.</p>
                <p>In noting with appreciation this affirmation of the policy of His Majesty’s
                    Government, I take pleasure in assuring you that the principle to which
                    reference is made is likewise a cardinal feature of the foreign policy of the
                    United States.</p>
                <p>I am, my dear Mr. Minister,</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
